# StoryTime Phase 8C — OPTIONAL vendor telemetry export credentials TEMPLATE.
#
# This is a COMMITTED TEMPLATE containing only obvious placeholders. To use the
# optional vendor export profiles:
#
#     cp config/vendor.secret.env.example config/vendor.secret.env
#     # then edit config/vendor.secret.env with your real vendor values
#
# config/vendor.secret.env is git-ignored (the *.secret.env pattern in
# .gitignore) and must NEVER be committed. It is read ONLY by the optional
# vendor override compose files. If you do not use vendor export you do not
# need to create it at all, and the default local-only stack is unaffected.
#
# ONE SHARED TEMPLATE, TWO INDEPENDENT PROFILES. There are two mutually
# exclusive vendor overrides — docker-compose.vendor.dynatrace.yml and
# docker-compose.vendor.newrelic.yml — and each reads this same file. Fill in
# ONLY the section for the vendor you are activating; the other vendor's values
# may stay as REPLACE-... placeholders. The Dynatrace override reads only the
# DYNATRACE_* values and the New Relic override reads only the NEWRELIC_*
# values, so unused placeholders are simply never referenced.
#
# SECRET SAFETY (Architecture Baseline 23.6, 23.7): every value below is an
# OBVIOUS PLACEHOLDER. This repository contains no real endpoint, token,
# tenant ID, account ID, or license key anywhere. The `.invalid` TLD (RFC 2606
# reserved) guarantees the placeholder endpoints are non-routable. Replace each
# value in your private copy; never commit the filled-in file.

# --- Dynatrace (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# OTLP/HTTP ingest endpoint of YOUR Dynatrace environment. The exact URL is in
# your Dynatrace documentation; it ends in /api/v2/otlp. Replace the whole
# value below (the .invalid host is a deliberately non-routable placeholder).
DYNATRACE_OTLP_ENDPOINT=https://REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-DYNATRACE-ENVIRONMENT.example.invalid/api/v2/otlp
# A Dynatrace API token with OTLP ingest scopes. REPLACE THIS PLACEHOLDER.
DYNATRACE_API_TOKEN=REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-DYNATRACE-API-TOKEN

# --- New Relic (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# New Relic OTLP/HTTP ingest endpoint. The correct regional endpoint is in your
# New Relic documentation. Replace the whole value below.
NEWRELIC_OTLP_ENDPOINT=https://REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-NEWRELIC-OTLP-ENDPOINT.example.invalid
# Your New Relic license (ingest) key. REPLACE THIS PLACEHOLDER.
NEWRELIC_LICENSE_KEY=REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-NEWRELIC-LICENSE-KEY
